item.title: Router i-p?
item.dc:creator: @Hikaru Hikaru
item.description:
@Hikaru wrote:

Go to Command Prompt (Start > Program Files > Accessories > Command Prompt) and type in ipconfig. The ‘Default Gateway’ is your server IP. Then try to log into it by putting “http://(yourip)” and typing in your username and password.
